This paper deals with the problem of detecting and preventing clickbaits in online news media, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.IR (Information Retrieval), which deals with the retrieval of information from large collections of unstructured data, such as text. The paper also involves text classification and sentiment analysis, which are common tasks in the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper deals with user preferences and personalization, which are relevant to the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper involves the use of browser extensions and user interfaces, which are relevant to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
